HEADWORD: Clericalism
<hw>Cler"ic*al*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An excessive
devotion to the interests of the sacerdotal order; undue influence of
the clergy; sacerdotalism.</def>⟦br⟧
